"'''One Last Night in the Mos Eisley Cantina: The Tale of the Wolfman and the Lamproid'''" is a short story written by [[Judith Reeves-Stevens|Judith]] and [[Garfield Reeves-Stevens]] for ''[[Tales from the Mos Eisley Cantina]]'', which was published in [[July]] [[1995]] by [[Bantam Spectra]]. It tells the tale of [[Shistavanen/Legends|Shistavanen]] [[Lak Sivrak/Legends|Lak Sivrak]] and Florn [[Lamproid/Legends|Lamproid]] [[Dice Ibegon/Legends|Dice Ibegon]]. The story takes place across the time span of the [[original trilogy]].

==Plot summary==
During the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], [[Lak Sivrak/Legends|Lak Sivrak's]] crippled [[X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing fighter]] crashes into the [[Endor/Legends|Endor]] [[Forest/Legends|forests]]. Before he [[Death/Legends|dies]], he experiences time-bending flashbacks to the first time he met his beloved, a [[Lamproid|Florn Lamproid]] named [[Dice Ibegon/Legends|Dice Ibegon]]. He recalls her death during the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]] before realizing that these visions are part of becoming one with [[The Force/Legends|the Force]].

==Continuity==
This peculiar story had [[Lak Sivrak/Legends|Lak]] reexperience the past with knowledge of the future, as well as the ability to alter his past. When he came to understand these visions as part of the process of his [[Death/Legends|death]], he and the spirit of [[Dice Ibegon/Legends|Dice]] joined "three friends" awaiting them within [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. The implication is that the trio consists of [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]], [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin]], the [[Force ghost/Legends|Force spirits]] from the end of [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Return of the Jedi'']] ([[1983]]). It is now understood that such Force spirits were the results of lessons from the teachings of the [[Shaman of the Whills/Legends|Shaman of the Whills]] via [[Qui-Gon Jinn/Legends|Qui-Gon Jinn]]; thus it follows that Dice was also privy to such arcane knowledge.<ref name="TERC" />

